<html>
<head>
    <title>For You ❤️</title>
    <style>
        body {
            background-color: #0d0d0d;
            color: #f5f5f5;
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            text-align: center;
            padding: 50px;
        }
        h1 { font-size: 40px; }
        h2 { color: #ff4d6d; }
        p { font-size: 18px; line-height: 1.6; }
        .date { margin-top: 30px; color: #aaa; }
        a {
            display: block;
            margin-top: 40px;
            color: #ff4d6d;
            text-decoration: none;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>

    <!-- EDIT THIS ONLY -->
    <h1>Day 1</h1>

    <h2>For you, I'd say...</h2>

    <p>
       if you love the sun , i'll burn forever<br>
if you love the moon , i'll shine forever<br>
i would find myself doomed enough, if i cant make you mine forever<br>
i love your laugh , i really do <br>
i see you looking at the moon , only to forget who is who<br>
i get lost in your eyes , to forget the concept of time<br>
inseperable by death, i'd find you in every lifetime<br>

    </p>

    <div class="date">April 5, 2026</div>
    <!-- END -->

    <a id="nextLink">Next →</a>

    <script>
        let dayText = document.querySelector("h1").innerText;
        let dayNumber = parseInt(dayText.replace("Day ", ""));
        let nextDay = dayNumber + 1;

        document.getElementById("nextLink").href = "day" + nextDay + ".html";
    </script>

